      "rich_text_43ezML": {
        "type": "rich-text",
        "disabled": true,
        "name": "Rich text",
        "settings": {
          "section_title": "",
          "text": "<p>Hannah Watts (b.1997) is a multidisciplinary artist based in London. She studied fine art at Edinburgh College of Art, The Florence Academy of Art, and graphic design at Shillington College. She uses a combination of these different mediums within her work. Graphic design plays a key role in her drawing style, using geometric shapes and patterns.</p><p>Silo Studio is a design studio consisting of Hannah’s artwork as well as homewares she has designed. It has become a space for Hannah to play; experimenting with different mediums and ideas and collaborating with like minded creatives.</p><p>Hannah’s inspiration largely derives from the tropics; namely the African landscape, both natural and architectural as well as from the craft originating there, particularly the textiles. Hannah likes to make up ‘dreamworlds’ within her designs, creating exaggerated versions of natural elements, particularly the plants and flowers within our landscape, and using pattern as a constant reference.</p><p>With a strong interest in hand made craft everything has either been created in house by Hannah, or designed and made by specialist artisans.</p><p></p><h2>EXHIBITIONS</h2><h3>South Africa</h3><p>'A Celebration of Cloth, into Clay', Chandler House, Cape Town, 21st February 2026</p><h3>UK</h3><p>'New Makers 2026', Toast, May 2026 - April 2027</p><p>'Summer Exhibition' at The Gallery at Green and Stone, 28th July - 28th August 2025</p><p>'The Spirit of Charleston', Watts Contemporary Gallery, 6th February - 6th April 2025</p><p>'GEOMETRIC TROPICANA', J/M Gallery, 4th-9th July 2024</p><p>'Re-Imagine', Gallery 8, 8th-13th January 2024</p><p>Eastwood Fine Art, Winter Exhibition, December 2020</p><h2>REPRESENTATION</h2><p><a href=\"https://www.toa.st/collections/hannah-watts-ceramics\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"TOAST\">TOAST</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.wsjgallery.com/artists/340-hannah-watts/works/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"WSJ Gallery\">WSJ Gallery</a></p><p><a href=\"https://chandlerhouse.co.za/exhibtion/hannah-watts/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Chandler House\">Chandler House (Cape Town)</a></p><p><a href=\"https://mah-gallery.com/hannah-watts\" target=\"_blank\">M.A.H Gallery</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.wonderingpeople.com/pages/home-collection\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"WONDERING PEOPLE\">Wondering People</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.felt-collections.com/shop/plates\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Felt\">FELT</a></p><p><a href=\"https://birdiefortescue.co.uk/collections/hannah-watts\" target=\"_blank\">Birdie Fortescue</a></p><p></p>",
          "text_size": "medium"
        }
      },
      "feature_row_UXd3jB": {
        "type": "feature-row",
        "disabled": true,
        "name": "Image with text",
        "settings": {
          "image": "shopify://shop_images/IMG_6225.jpg",
          "layout": "left",
          "full_width": true,
          "color_scheme": "none",
          "title": "",
          "text": "<p>Hannah Watts (b.1997) is a multidisciplinary artist based in London. She studied fine art at Edinburgh College of Art, The Florence Academy of Art, and graphic design at Shillington College. She uses a combination of these different mediums within her work. Graphic design plays a key role in her drawing style, using geometric shapes and patterns.</p><p>Silo Studio is a design studio consisting of Hannah’s artwork as well as homewares she has designed. It has become a space for Hannah to play; experimenting with different mediums and ideas and collaborating with like minded creatives.</p><p>Hannah’s inspiration largely derives from the tropics; namely the African landscape, both natural and architectural as well as from the craft originating there, particularly the textiles. Hannah likes to make up ‘dreamworlds’ within her designs, creating exaggerated versions of natural elements, particularly the plants and flowers within our landscape, and using pattern as a constant reference.</p><p>With a strong interest in hand made craft everything has either been created in house by Hannah, or designed and made by specialist artisans.</p>",
          "button_label": "",
          "button_link": ""
        }
      },
